---
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
import { SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../data/site';
// [PENDENTE: revisão jurídica; entidade controladora, endereço registrado e
// prazos de retenção a confirmar]
---

<Legal
  title="Privacy Policy | MLogTech"
  description="How MLogTech collects, uses and protects personal data, and the rights you have under UK GDPR."
  h1="Privacy Policy."
  updated="July 17, 2026 (draft)"
>
  <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    MLogTech provides delivery management software. For data you submit on this website (for
    example, the demo or contact forms), MLogTech is the controller. For operational data our
    customers process through the platform (their customers' names, addresses, signatures), the
    customer is the controller and MLogTech is a processor acting on instructions.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Data we collect on this website</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Contact details you send us: name, work email, phone, message content.</li>
    <li>Operational context you volunteer, such as fleet size or delivery volume.</li>
    <li>Technical basics needed to serve the site, such as IP address in server logs.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>This site does not run advertising trackers.</p>

  <h2>3. What we use it for</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Responding to demo and contact requests (legitimate interest / pre-contract steps).</li>
    <li>Providing and securing the service for customers (contract).</li>
    <li>Meeting legal obligations, such as accounting records (legal obligation).</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Data in the platform</h2>
  <p>
    Delivery records processed through MLogTech (addresses, proof of delivery, driver locations
    during shifts) are processed on behalf of the customer that operates the account, under data
    processing terms. We do not sell personal data, and we do not use customer operational data
    for purposes other than providing the service.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Website enquiries are kept for as long as needed to handle the conversation and reasonable
    follow-up. Platform data is retained while the account is active and deleted or returned after
    termination, subject to legal retention duties.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    We share data with the service providers needed to run the product (such as cloud hosting),
    under contracts that restrict their use of it. We do not share personal data with third
    parties for their own marketing.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
  <p>
    Under UK GDPR you can request access, correction, deletion, restriction or portability of your
    personal data, and object to certain processing. Write to
    <a class="textlink" href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a> and we will respond
    within the statutory period. You can also complain to the Information Commissioner's Office
    (ICO).
  </p>

  <h2>8. Security</h2>
  <p>
    Practices are described on the <a class="textlink" href="/security/">security page</a>:
    encryption in transit, access control, backups and responsible disclosure.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We will post updates to this policy here, with the date above. Material changes affecting
    customers will be communicated directly.
  </p>
</Legal>
